			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Reporting to the Vice President, Finance, this is a hands-on role that provides an exciting opportunity to influence the future direction of the accounting department in a start-up company poised for growth.</p>
<p>
Key responsibilities include:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Maintain the Chart of Accounts and General Ledgers, ensuring accuracy and appropriate controls over accounting transactions</li>
<li>
Oversee A/P, accruals, journal entries and reconciliations prepared by the Senior Accountant</li>
<li>
Consolidate and prepare monthly, quarterly and annual financial statements</li>
<li>
Support quarterly and annual reporting process as required, including drafting of note disclosures and preparation of working papers for auditors</li>
<li>
Development of monthly management reports and financial analysis to support the needs of a growing enterprise</li>
<li>
Maintain capital asset sub ledger</li>
<li>
Maintain stock-based compensation records using StockVantage software</li>
<li>
Assist in the implementation of a new ERP system</li>
</ul>
<p>
Requirements:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelors degree combined with a professional accounting designation</li>
<li>
Minimum of 2 years post-designation experience displaying leadership and flexibility in a changing environment and success in a similar role</li>
<li>
Good knowledge of IFRS</li>
<li>
Public company experience, ideally in the high tech industry</li>
<li>
Experience with implementing and using ERP systems</li>
<li>
Strong written and verbal communication skills</li>
<li>
Detail-oriented and able to coordinate multiple activities at the same time</li>
<li>
Strong interpersonal skills</li>
<li>
Ability to meet goals and deliver accurately within tight deadlines</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
